 ), presiding in the middle part of his reign over a period of unparalleled French power and prosperity. In modern times Louis is also found in the English-speaking world (usually pronounced ‘<b>loo</b>-ee’). In Britain the Anglicized form   Lewis   is rather more common, whereas in America the reverse is true."],"variants":[{"name":"Lewie","meanings":["Anglicized spelling of   Louis  , or a pet form of   Lewis ."]},{"name":"Louie","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Lewie   or   Louis  , currently in fashion."]},{"name":"Lewi","meanings":["form, since the Middle Ages, of the French name   Louis .  In modern use it is also in part a transferred use of the surname derived from this given name, or from Anglicized forms of Gaelic <i>Mac Lughaidh</i> ‘son of  <b>Lughaidh</b> ’  or Welsh Llewelyn ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Louis D'HEBUTERNE was born in 1197, in France, his father, Gautier D'HEBUTERNE, was 33 and his mother, Isabeau DE BERLES, was 16. He had at least 1 daughter with Marie De BAYENCOURT. He died in 1259, at the age of 62."},"et":{"1197–1259":"1197–1259","1208–1249":"1208–1249","1225–1284":"1225–1284","1164–1221":"1164–1221","1181–1238":"1181–1238","1238":"1238","1249":"1249","1259":"1259","1225":"1225","1221":"1221","1197":"1197","1164":"1164","1284":"1284","1181":"1181","1208":"1208","Hamelincourt, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France":"Hamelincourt, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Hébuterne, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France":"Hébuterne, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1197–1259":"1197–1259","1208–1249":"1208–1249","1225–1284":"1225–1284","1164–1221":"1164–1221","1181–1238":"1181–1238","1238":"1238","1249":"1249","1259":"1259","1225":"1225","1221":"1221","1197":"1197","1164":"1164","1284":"1284","1181":"1181","1208":"1208","Hamelincourt, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France":"Hamelincourt, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Ranska","Hébuterne, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France":"Hébuter